html - hypertext markup language
it is a markup language that is used to create strucute for an webpage
invented by tim berners lee in 1991
it acts as a skeleton
it contains series of elements that are represente by tags


<resword>content</resword>      element ---opentag + contennt + closing tag

container or pair tags
<h1>some content</h1>


empty tags or void tags 
<img />


basic structure of html
<!DOCTYPE html>---declartion ---it defines type of doc and version
<html>
<head>
<title>first webpage </title>
</head>---to define title, meta and third party links
<body>

headings
 <h1>heading</h1>
  <h2>heading</h2>
  <h3>heading</h3>
  <h4>heading</h4>
  <h5>heading</h5>
  <h6>heading</h6>

  paragraph
  <p>some para content </p>

  images
  //absolute
  <img src='https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/sun-sets-behind-mountain-ranges-600nw-2479236003.jpg'>
//relative url
  <img src='img1.webp'>

  attributes 
  attributes provides extra information about an tag
  and controls the behaviour which comes is key value pairs
</body>---content
</html>----root element 

